column3: Neil Diamond
column4: Today Neil Diamond announces that he will be extending his 50th anniversary tour to the UK and Europe in 2017. Celebrating his unparalleled career, the tour will come to the UK in October for six stunning arena dates.In addition to his upcoming tour, UME and Capitol Music Group have announced the March 31st release of Neil Diamond: The 50th Anniversary Collection, a celebratory music package that includes 50 songs that range 50 years in Diamond’s career. Throughout an illustrious and wide-ranging musical career, Neil Diamond has sold over 130 million albums worldwide and has charted 37 Top 40 singles and 16 Top 10 albums. A Grammy Award-winning artist, Diamond is a member of the Rock & Roll Hall of Fame, the Songwriters Hall of Fame and a recipient of the Sammy Cahn Lifetime Achievement Award, one of the highest honours bestowed upon songwriters. Diamond’s many other achievements include a Golden Globe award, 13 Grammy nominations and 2009’s NARAS MusiCares Person of the Year award. In 2011, Diamond received the prestigious Kennedy Center Honor for his lifetime of contributions to American culture.

column3: Neil Diamond
column4: 50TH ANNIVERSARY WORLD TOURTickets on sale Friday 27th January 2017 at 10amLive Nation and MCD Productions are honoured to announce – on his birthday – that musical icon, Grammy award winner and Rock & Roll Hall of Fame Member, Neil Diamond will be extending his 50th anniversary tour to the UK and Europe in 2017.“Neil Diamond is more than just a music icon. His singular artistry and talent has left an indelible mark on American culture and has helped shape the sound of popular music for five decades” says Michael Rapino, President and CEO of Live Nation Entertainment. “Live Nation is honoured to be a part of bringing his 50 year anniversary tour to fans around the world.”In addition to his upcoming tour, UME and Capitol Music Group have announced the March 31st release of Neil Diamond: The 50th Anniversary Collection, a celebratory music package that includes 50 songs that range 50 years in Diamond’s career. Under the supervision of Diamond, the anniversary set includes his own handpicked songs and a carefully curated 50 page booklet with new liner notes.Throughout an illustrious and wide-ranging musical career, Neil Diamond has sold over 130 million albums worldwide and has charted 37 Top 40 singles and 16 Top 10 albums. A Grammy Award-winning artist, Diamond is a member of the Rock & Roll Hall of Fame, the Songwriters Hall of Fame and a recipient of the Sammy Cahn Lifetime Achievement Award, one of the highest honours bestowed upon songwriters. Diamond’s many other achievements include a Golden Globe award, 13 Grammy nominations and 2009’s NARAS MusiCares Person of the Year award. In 2011, Diamond received the prestigious Kennedy Center Honor for his lifetime of contributions to American culture.

column3: Hound High Tea Benefitting The Lucky Diamond Critical Care Ward At The Humane Society of New York
column4: SAVE THE DATE! Animal Fair Media’s Wendy Diamond is hosting the first ever “Hound High Tea” in history this July. Dames, Dapper men and Dogs will be sipping refined tea and eating tasty finger sandwich treats for a good cause! All proceeds from the event will benefit The Humane Society of New York's Lucky Diamond Critical Care Ward.Wendy’s beloved sidekick of more than 12 years passed last July from canine spleen cancer. In Lucky’s honor, Wendy created and hosted The Most Expensive Pet Wedding in History, which earned her a Guinness World Record for the Most Expensive Wedding.The event paid tribute to Lucky’s service, and the countless animals she helped to find a loving home over the past decade. All proceeds from the event were donated to the creation of The Humane Society of New York’s Lucky Diamond Critical Care Ward. The critical care ward will carry on Lucky’s legacy of saving and helping animals in dire need, and provide pet parents and animals affordable critical health care that they might not have received otherwise.Wendy Diamond is the perfect animal advocate and pet-lifestyle expert to celebrate a high tea; her mother was born and raised in the UK! Not only that, Wendy was awarded a Guinness World Record for the Longest Curtsy Relay - the Queen would be proud. And for those of you wondering if dogs should even drink tea, no worries, Wendy will be serving an exclusive special tea designed and brewed for canines only!!Wendy’s bark story started in 1999, after she adopted her Russian Blue cat, Pasha and Maltese, Lucky. She was inspired to create Animal Fair Media, and became the premiere entrepreneur to combine the pet industry, animal rescue, celebrity, and media! Wendy Diamond coined the term “pet lifestyle” and designed a career through her passion for helping animals and business. When she started Animal Fair Media the number of animals euthanized annually in the U.S. dropped by 58%, from 12 million to 5 million.Wendy was inspired to create premiere benefits featuring guest appearances by celebrities, with  proceeds benefiting animal rescue organizations across the country/world. These events include; Paws For Style, Yappy Hour, Halloween Pet Costume Party and Toys For Dogs. Animal Organizations all over the world have emuliated these events to raise money and awareness for the benefit of animal rescue and welfare.The “Hound High Tea” charity event will celebrate with 200 dog parents, animal rescue advocates, business leaders, celebrities, and media personalities that believe in giving back. Their dogs will eagerly join them for high tea and yummy treats! You never know we may even receive another Guinness World Record for the largest Hound High tea Party In History!

column3: Neil Diamond - 50 Year Anniversary World Tour at Ziggo Dome
column4: Neil Diamond zit 50 jaar in het vak. De hoogste tijd dus om terug te blikken op de vele hoogtepunten uit zijn muzikale loopbaan en dat doet de Amerikaanse singer-songwriter met een heuse '50 Year Anniversary World Tour’. Maak je op voor een walk down memory lane vol iconische songs, zoals ‘Solitary Man’, ‘Sweet Caroline’ en ‘I Am… I Said’.

column3: Crazy Diamond - The Pink Floyd Tribute
column4: Crazy Diamond - The Pink Floyd TributeCRAZY DIAMOND haben sich einen Namen als originalgetreue Pink-Floyd-Tribute-Band verschafft, die es dennoch versteht, der Musik ihren persönlichen Stempel aufzudrücken. Die Songs kommen live oftmals kraftvoller daher, als man es sich von den Alben her gewohnt ist, da und dort gekonnt mit einer eigenen Note versehen. Das im 2016 erschienene Dreifachalbum „Live at Augusta Raurica“, von Presse und Fans hochgelobt, repräsentiert eindrücklich das akribische Schaffen der Eidgenossen, deren Wirken übrigens bis ins Floyd-Lager nach London durchgedrungen ist. Crazy Diamond ist keine 0815 Hitfabrik. Klassiker wie Time oder Wish you were here dürfen natürlich nicht fehlen. Immer wieder aber gräbt die Band längst vergessene Perlen aus, die selbst die Original-Floyds seit Urzeiten nicht mehr spielen. Für ihren Auftritt im Kofmehl rührt die Band mit grosser Kehle an. Nebst fettem Sound darf eine intelligente Lichtshow, untermalt mit eindrücklichen Visuals, nicht fehlen. Die Zuhörer kommen in den Genuss von 200% Pink Floyd!Ticketpreis:CHF 38 (inkl. Gebühren)Mindestalter:16 Jahre (od. in Begleitung eines Elternteils)Zeitplan:18:30 Uhr Öffnung Vorplatz19:00 Uhr Türöffnung20:00 Uhr BeginnFoodtruck:Ab 18:30 Uhr verwöhnt s-mobil auf dem Kofmehlareal die Gäste mit einem breiten Essens- & Getränkeangebot zu fairen Preisen. Weitere Infos:http://kofmehl.net/programm/crazy-diamond/Direktlink zum Vorverkauf:https://www.starticket.ch/de/tickets/crazy-diamond-20180309-2000-kulturfabrik-kofmehl-solothurn

column3: Neil Diamond - 50 Year Anniversary World Tour | Sportpaleis
column4: Een feestelijke dag voor Neil Diamond! Terwijl hij vandaag zijn eigen 76ste verjaardag viert, kondigt hij aan dat de tournee naar aanleiding van de 50ste verjaardag van zijn carrière nu ook naar Europa komt. De ‘50th Anniversary Tour’ houdt op donderdag 28 september halt in het Sportpaleis.Neil Diamond is één groot succesverhaal. Een Grammy Award, een Golden Globe, een opname in de Songwriters Hall of Fame en in 2011 zelfs nog in de Rock and Roll Hall of Fame en ook de zéér prestigieuze Sammy Cahn Lifetime Achievement Award; Diamond heeft het allemaal op zijn naam staan. De Amerikaanse levende legende heeft zijn internationale succes te danken aan zijn charisma, een ijzersterke live reputatie en natuurlijk een berg onsterfelijke hits. Sweet Caroline, Girl, You'll Be A Woman Soon, Solitary Man, I Am...I Said, Cracklin' Rosie... De lijst is eindeloos, de songs tijdloos.5 decennia actief in de muziekindustrie. Dat is een jubileum dat Neil Diamond op gepaste manier wil vieren. Hij brengt daarom de ‘50th Anniversary Collection’ uit, een unieke verzameling van 50 zorgvuldig geselecteerde eigen songs uit 50 jaar carrière. Daarnaast is er ook een feestelijke wereldtournee. Neil Diamond brengt zijn ‘50th Anniversary Tour’ op donderdag 28 september naar het Sportpaleis in Antwerpen.--C’est un jour de fête pour Neil Diamond! L’artiste a décidé d’annoncer le jour de ses 76 printemps l’ajout d’un volet européen à sa tournée internationale qui marque ses 50 ans de carrière. Le volet européen de son ‘50th Anniversary Tour’ passera par le Sportpaleis d’Anvers le jeudi 28 septembre ! Neil Diamond cumule les prix et récompenses qui honorent une carrière splendide: un Grammy Award, un Golden Globe, une entrée au Songwriters Hall of Fames et, en 2011, au Rock and Roll Hall of Fame mais également un très honorable Sammy Cahn Lifetime Achievement Award. La légende vivante américaine doit son succès international tant à son charisme qu'à la solide réputation de ses performances live et, bien entendu, à ses innombrables tubes : Sweet Caroline, Girl, You'll Be A Woman Soon, Solitary Man, I Am...I Said, Cracklin' Rosie... Cette liste est sans fin et les titres intemporels.  5 florissantes décennies passées dans l’industrie de la musique c’est un anniversaire que Neil Diamond veut fêter comme il se doit avec une nouvelle sortie intitulée ‘50th Anniversary Collection’. Il s’agit d’une compilation unique de 50 titres soigneusement sélectionnés parmi tous les morceaux de ses 50 années de carrière. Neil Diamond et son  ‘50th Anniversary Tour’ seront au Sportpaleis d’Anvers le jeudi 28 septembre.

column3: 24th Annual UAC Fall Fundraiser Presented by Black Diamond
column4: The event you have been waiting for since last fall is on.  Block out your calendars, reserve a babysitter, and change that trip to Des Moines to a video conference. 1000 friends, dinner from Utah Food Service, beverages from Uinta Brewing, raffle, silent auction, music by Herban Empire, raffle. You know the deal. Help us help you.  This is our biggest fundraising event of the year and helps pay for avalanche forecasting and education.New this year! We have switched to a mobile silent auction platform called GiveSmart. Now bidding, winning and supporting your favorite avalanche center is even easier. When you purchase your tickets in advance you will automatically be registered through GiveSmart and set and ready to bid come party night.Tickets: $ 40.00 in advance/ $ 45.00 at the door.Students age 25 and younger with valid student ID can buy tickets at the door for $25Purchasing an advance ticket will put you on the will call list. You won't get a paper ticket.Advance ticket sales will end at noon on Sept 13.  You can buy tickets at the door for $5 more.You can buy your tickets here: https://uac2017.auction-bid.org/microsite/New This The fine print:Current and future backcounty users age 12 and under are welcome and free.  They can buy a meal ticket for $10 if they plan to eat.Students age 25 and younger with valid student ID can buy tickets at the door for $25Please leave your dog home.This event will be held rain or shine.  We are mountain people and a little rain doesn't scare us.If you have a product or service that you'd like to donate to the silent auction or raffle, let us know

column3: Robot Soul: Boogs 7 Hour Set
column4: Tickets on sale now via: https://robot_soul.eventbrite.com.auWe have declared the last Friday in September as a Robot Soul Public Holiday because let’s face it, everybody needs a day off to dance! After such an overwhelming response to the first Robot Soul party, we are proud to announce that Boogs is planning to take us on another epic journey to raise the vibrations.  Keeping with his part man, part machine ethos Boogs has promised AT LEAST SEVEN HOURS of Robot Soul for your listening and dancing pleasure, all this while enjoying a 360-degree view of the Melbourne city skyline.If you all remember the last Robot Soul party, tickets sold out quick. Don’t get left behind.  #RobotSoul#RaisingTheVibration
